# Script edited with Filtration - https://github.com/ben-wallis/Filtration
# This loot filter script uses Neversink's lootfilter as a basis for many areas, but employs further differentiation of items in an attempt to eliminate as many items from the screen as possible that will not be picked up.
# 
# New color coding has been introduced, here's a breakdown:
# Text:
# - 75+ items have a slight reddish hue on their text.
# Background:
# - Good and bad bases are differentiated by background color (red hue vs green hue), this is unchanged from Neversink's filter.
# - Things like flasks, chrome items, rock breakers etc. get a grey background for attention.
# - Chanceable items get a violet hue on their background.
# Border color:
# - Flasks have a touch of blue on their borders.
# - For leveling, items that should have priority for being ID'd get a beige border. This also applies to e.g. harbinger bows in maps.
# - Magic jewelry gets a dark green border to signal it might be worth filling spare slots in your inventory with. Either vendor them unid for transmutes, or id for alt shards (I'm currently testing whether this results in profit).
# - High level normal/magic loot is given progressively more saturated pink-red border highlights.
# 
# For Warbands:
# Every time you kill a pack of warbands, hold your "show all items" key. Magic boots, helmets and gloves will be highlighted in their borders by their respective warband. For example, if you killed redblades, you should ID all magic helmets, those will have a red border.
# This part is also taken from Neversink's filter, although I fixed the missing border color for the boots.

